locality.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="68DEC5F83D7FFF98FF4DFC3FFB49FBE9" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="207B96733D7FFF98FF4DFC3FFB49FBE9" blockId="12.[151,1437,906,1725]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D7FFF98FF4DFC3FFEA9FB86" bold="true" box="[199,322,1014,1040]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of 
<taxonomicName id="E7C4EDF03D7FFF98FE3AFC3EFD69FB87" authority="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira, 2021" authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira" authorityYear="2021" box="[432,642,1015,1041]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Patrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barbacoas" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D7FFF98FE3AFC3EFD69FB87" box="[432,642,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Patrera barbacoas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="12B04A613D7FFF98FD03FC3EFD2CFB87" bold="true" box="[649,711,1015,1041]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="0983F71A3D7FFF98FD03FC3EFD2CFB87" box="[649,711,1015,1041]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
resemble those of 
<taxonomicName id="E7C4EDF03D7FFF98FC12FC3EFBFEFB87" authority="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira, 2021" authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira" authorityYear="2021" box="[920,1045,1015,1041]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Patrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="platnicki" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D7FFF98FC12FC3EFBFEFB87" box="[920,1045,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">P. platnicki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="12B04A613D7FFF98FB91FC3EFBB2FB87" bold="true" box="[1051,1113,1015,1041]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="0983F71A3D7FFF98FB91FC3EFBB2FB87" box="[1051,1113,1015,1041]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by having the abdomen with several dark patches and subquadrate retrolateral tibial apophysis (
<figureCitation id="B8FF8AF63D7FFF98FCF0FBD2FC35FBA1" box="[890,990,1051,1079]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1479,1503]" captionTargetBox="[163,1429,181,1451]" captionTargetId="figure-27@22.[151,1436,181,1455]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 10A–D. Patrera platnicki n. sp. Male (ICN-Ar-5673): A habitus, dorsal view; B palp, retroventral view; C palp, ventral view; D palp, retrolateral view. Scale bars: A: 2mm; B–D: 0.5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468403" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468403/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Fig. 10B</figureCitation>
̅D), but can be distinguished by the retrolateral tibial apophysis narrower (larger and wider in 
<taxonomicName id="E7C4EDF03D7FFF98FC88FBF6FC94FBCF" authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira" authorityYear="2021" box="[770,895,1087,1113]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Patrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="platnicki">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D7FFF98FC88FBF6FC94FBCF" box="[770,895,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">P. platnicki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and apically subrounded, and embolus inserted on the base of the tegulum (inserted near the middle of tegulum in 
<taxonomicName id="E7C4EDF03D7FFF98FC08FBAAFBEBFBEB" authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira" authorityYear="2021" box="[898,1024,1123,1149]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Patrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="platnicki">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D7FFF98FC08FBAAFBEBFBEB" box="[898,1024,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">P. platnicki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<figureCitation id="B8FF8AF63D7FFF98FB93FBAAFB84FBE9" box="[1049,1135,1123,1151]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1903,1927]" captionTargetBox="[160,1422,561,1876]" captionTargetId="figure-148@13.[151,1436,561,1880]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 5A–D. Patrera barbacoas n. sp. Male (ICN-Ar-10604): A habitus, dorsal view; B palp, retroventral view; C palp, ventral view; D palp, retrolateral view. Scale bars: A: 2mm; B–D: 0.5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468393" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468393/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Fig. 5B</figureCitation>
̅D).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="68DEC5F83D7FFF98FF4DFB4FFE49F90F" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="description">
<paragraph id="207B96733D7FFF98FF4DFB4FFE33F9E1" blockId="12.[151,1437,906,1725]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D7FFF98FF4DFB4FFEB2FB36" bold="true" box="[199,345,1158,1184]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="12B04A613D7FFF98FEE8FB4EFE77FB37" box="[354,412,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Male</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus id="FF7F28D13D7FFF98FE27FB4EFDF1FB37" box="[429,538,1159,1185]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Holotype</typeStatus>
, ICN-Ar-10604). Carapace brownish, darker on the cephalic region (
<figureCitation id="B8FF8AF63D7FFF98FAB9FB4EFA7BFB37" box="[1331,1424,1158,1185]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1903,1927]" captionTargetBox="[160,1422,561,1876]" captionTargetId="figure-148@13.[151,1436,561,1880]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 5A–D. Patrera barbacoas n. sp. Male (ICN-Ar-10604): A habitus, dorsal view; B palp, retroventral view; C palp, ventral view; D palp, retrolateral view. Scale bars: A: 2mm; B–D: 0.5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468393" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468393/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
). Chelicerae dark brown. Labium and endites brown. Sternum yellowish. Legs yellow, darkest from tibiae to tarsi. Abdomen pale yellow with black spots and black setae; ventrally pale yellow. Spinnerets yellow (
<figureCitation id="B8FF8AF63D7FFF98FB79FB06FAA4FB7F" box="[1267,1359,1230,1257]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1903,1927]" captionTargetBox="[160,1422,561,1876]" captionTargetId="figure-148@13.[151,1436,561,1880]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 5A–D. Patrera barbacoas n. sp. Male (ICN-Ar-10604): A habitus, dorsal view; B palp, retroventral view; C palp, ventral view; D palp, retrolateral view. Scale bars: A: 2mm; B–D: 0.5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468393" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468393/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
). Total length 8.12, carapace length 3.76, width 4.47, high 1.81. Clypeus height 0.21. Eye diameters and interdistances: AME 0.15, ALE 0.27, PME 0.24, PLE 0.27; AME–AME 0.34, AME–ALE 0.50, PME–PME 0.67, PME–PLE 0.67, ALE–PLE 0.57. Chelicerae 1.8 long, four promarginal teeth, five retromarginal denticles. Leg measurements: leg I—femur 4.35/ patella 1.68/ tibia 4.76/ metatarsus 3.41/ tarsus 2.01/ total 16.21; II—4.32/ 1.65/ 4.78/ 2.76/ 1.9/ 15.41; III—3.37/ 1.52/ 2.99/ 3.24/ 1.12/ 12.24; IV—4.08/ 1.56/ 3.68/ 4.17/ 1.54/ 15.03. Leg spination: I—metatarsus v1-2-0, p0-1-0, r0-1-0; II—metatarsus v2-2-0, p1-1-0, r1-1-0; III— tibia d1-0-0, p0-1-1, r0-1-1, metatarsus p1- 2-2, r1-1-2; IV—tibia d1-0-0, p1-0-1, r1-1-1, metatarsus p1-2-2, r1-1-2. Abdomen: length 4.34, epigastric furrow 1.19 from tracheal spiracle, spiracle 1.77 from base of spinnerets. Palp: retrolateral tibial apophysis large with apical denticles; cymbium longer than tibia; subtegulum longer than wide with apically conical distal projection; tegulum longer than wide; median apophysis very short and basally situated; embolus long with narrow base, basally inserted on the tegulum (
<figureCitation id="B8FF8AF63D7FFF98FEC5F992FE4EF9E1" box="[335,421,1627,1655]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1903,1927]" captionTargetBox="[160,1422,561,1876]" captionTargetId="figure-148@13.[151,1436,561,1880]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 5A–D. Patrera barbacoas n. sp. Male (ICN-Ar-10604): A habitus, dorsal view; B palp, retroventral view; C palp, ventral view; D palp, retrolateral view. Scale bars: A: 2mm; B–D: 0.5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468393" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468393/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Fig. 5B</figureCitation>
̅D).
</paragraph>
